snippet: Hoping to push Egypt’s military rulers to disqualify Ahmed Shafik from the presidential runoff vote, his electoral rivals are planning further demonstrations.
abstract: Mohamed Morsi, presidential candidate of the Muslim Brotherhood, and two popular rivals eliminated before the runoff election have called for further street protests until Egypt's military rulers enforce legislation disqualifying Ahmed Shafik, former Pres Hosni Mubarak's last prime minister.
lead_paragraph: Hoping to push Egypt’s military rulers to disqualify Ahmed Shafik from the presidential runoff vote, his electoral rivals are planning further demonstrations.

headline.seo: More Protests Loom Since Egypt Election
headline.main: More Protests Loom in Egypt, Targeting Candidacy of Mubarak’s Prime Minister
headline.print_headline: More Protests Loom in Egypt, Targeting Candidacy of Mubarak’s Prime Minister
